## Conditions

1. **Contribution of Modifications**:
   - If you modify, enhance, or otherwise improve this software, you are required to contribute these changes back to the original project repository or submit them as a Pull Request (PR) for community use.
   - Modifications must be made publicly available under the same terms as this license.

2. **Open Source Requirement for Commercial Use**:
   - If you use this software or a modified version to generate revenue or as part of a commercial product, you are required to:
     - Make all changes and source code modifications publicly available under a recognized open-source license.
     - Contribute any improvements, enhancements, or changes back to the original project repository.

3. **Option for Private Modifications with One-Time Payment**:
   - If you wish to make modifications without sharing them publicly as open-source, you may contact the author for permission by making a one-time payment. This one-time payment, upon agreement, will grant you the right to keep your modifications private, waiving the open-source contribution requirement.
   - For inquiries about this option, please contact the author directly.

4. **Attribution**:
   - You must give appropriate credit to the original project, retain any existing copyright notices, and provide a link to the original repository.

